<TITLE> Azizul stresses greater global competitiveness </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam Thursday said enhancing global competitiveness must be a national priority. "We have to concentrate on improving business competitiveness," he said. "Quality products will enable us to uphold and improve our position in global competition," Azizul told the inaugural session of the Japan Trade Fair at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. The Japan-Bangladesh Chamber of Commerce and Industry organised the fair to display Japanese products for Bangladeshi consumers. The fair will run through to Dec 1. The finance adviser said the government was working to create a business-friendly atmosphere. "Many things from infrastructure development to the formation of the Better Business Forum have been done to improve the business and investment situation," he said. "The Regulatory Reforms Commission has been formed to help businesses," he said. Ambassador Masauki Inoue of Japan, FBCCI president Mir Nasir Hossain, and JBCCI president Hideo Ueno also spoke at the function. bdne
